solution.p:
To find where the graph intersects the y-axis, we need to evaluate at x=0. We have y = -2 (0)^2+5(0)+3 = 3, so that (0,3) is the y-intercept. Since the leading coefficient is negative, the parabola will open down.
The vertex can be found equidistant from the two x-intercepts. To find its x-coordinate, average \frac{-\frac{1}{2}+3}{2} = \frac{-1+6}{4} = \frac{5}{4}. To find the y-coordinate of the vertex, evaluate
y \amp= -2 \left(\frac{5}{4}\right)^2 + 5 \left(\frac{5}{4}\right)+ 3 \amp= -2 \left(\frac{25}{16}\right) + \frac{25}{4}+ 3 \amp= -\frac{50}{16} + \frac{25}{4}+ 3 \amp= -\frac{25}{8} + \frac{50}{8}+ \frac{24}{8} \amp= \frac{-25+50+24}{8} \amp= \frac{49}{8}
